      <div class="panel panel-primary">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          Content Mapping Principles
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
            <h4>Content may be <strong>retained</strong> when:</h4>
              <ol>
                <li class="recipe">Quantitative Criteria
                  <ol>
                    <li class="recipe">Page status code is 200 (live and available)</li>
                    <li class="recipe">More than 0 page views in analytics</li>
                    <li class="recipe">Average time on page is greater than 0:00</li>
                    <li class="recipe">Events older than 1/1/2017</li>
                    <li class="recipe">Is a PDF that does not require brand update
                      <ol>
                        <li class="recipe">Tyco.com security PDFs may be retained and assigned to Tyco.com</li>
                        <li class="recipe">Tyco PDFs assigned to JohnsonControls.com may require update</li>
                      </ol></li>
                  </ol></li>
                  <li class="recipe">Qualitative Notes
                    <ol>
                      <li class="recipe">Best represents the enterprise, brand, offering or insight for the region and language intended</li>
                      <li class="recipe">Is the only content available for a product, solution, service or insight</li>
                    </ol></li>
                </ol>
            <h4>Content may be <strong>updated</strong> when:</h4>
              <ol>
                <li class="recipe">Accurate, but requiring editorial adjustment for messaging targeted to audience or page purpose â€“ based on editorial review</li>
                <li class="recipe">Brand updates are required (ex: text or logo updates from Tyco to Johnson Controls, where appearing on JohnsonControls.com)</li>
              </ol>
            <h4>301 Redirects</h4>
              <ol>
                <li class="recipe">Will be identified on legacy sites, assigned a disposition with rules TBD by SEO team</li>
              </ol>
            <h4>Content will be <strong>retired</strong> when:</h4>
              <ol>
                <li class="recipe">Not active on site; Page Status Code < > 200</li>
                <li class="recipe">Duplicate</li>
                <li class="recipe">Not applicable to the current business approach</li>
              </ol>
